es the relationship between the party and the electorate in a post-coalition, post-Brexit, post-pandemic era. It offers a deep analysis of the electoral strategy that enabled growth and precipitated failure, explaining how and why the party got the coalition so wrong and plotting a potential future. Drawing on extensive survey data and original interviews with Lib Dem politicians and activists, the authors expertly capture the relationship between the party and voters, revealing the foundations of Liberal Democrat campaigning and performance in the search for credibility and viability. The Liberal Democrats remain contradictory: a minor party with ambitions to upset the status quo, a party that depends on decisive leadership but relies on grassroots activism to remain relevant. This book helps unravel these apparent contradictions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical partieszGreat BritainxPlatforms. 0aPolitical partieszGreat Britain. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh  aBlue Wall.  aBrexit.  aConservative–Liberal Democrat coalition.  aJo Swinson.  aLib Dems.  aLiberal Democrats.  aNick Clegg.  aausterity.  aelection campaigning.  athird-party politics.1 aCutts, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Andrew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRussell, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTownsley, Joshua Harry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTownsley, Joshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7